# Travel Studio Patterns

## Architecture Boundary

Puck owns composition and rendering. Domain truth (clients, trips, suppliers, pricing)
lives outside Puck and is referenced via `external` fields or `resolveData`.

## Component Organization

Components live under `config/components/` in four families:
- `structural/` -- layout containers with slots (DocumentSection, DaySection, SidebarLayout, CardGroup, Spacer, Divider)
- `travel/` -- trip content cards (TripHeader, TripOverview, StayCard, ActivityCard, TransportCard, PricingSummary)
- `context/` -- interpretive blocks (AdvisorInsight, IncludedFeatures)
- `conversion/` -- action blocks (PrimaryCTA)

## Component Contract

Every component must:
- Export a named `ComponentConfig` and a Props type
- Use `type: "slot"` for nested composition regions
- Set `allow`/`disallow` on slots via the config barrel (`config/index.ts`), not in the component file
- Check `puck.metadata?.target` for mode-aware rendering if the component behaves differently per mode
- Use inline styles (no CSS Modules in this app for now)

## Root Config

Root provides document-level fields: `title`, `documentMode`, `brandTheme`.
The `documentMode` flows to components via `metadata.target`.

## Data Persistence

Save/load uses a JSON file (`travel-data.json`) via the API route at `app/api/documents/route.ts`.
Seed data in `config/seed-data.ts` is the fallback when no saved data exists.

## Import Pattern

Import Puck types from `@/core` (resolved via tsconfig paths to `packages/core`).
Do NOT add `@puckeditor/core` to `package.json` dependencies.
